Start off with the fact that Apple isn=E2=80=99t doing anything new here: i=
ts products have always been predicated on integration generally, and the o=
nly meaningful change in Apple=E2=80=99s policies with regards to 3rd-party=
 apps has been to create the App Store in the first place. The situation wo=
uld be very different if Apple were locking its platform down after the fac=
t, but that isn=E2=80=99t really what has happened.

This is about consumers; the story with developers is very different, becau=
se App Tracking Transparency absolutely did change the deal in an economica=
lly destructive way for developers, and to Apple=E2=80=99s economic benefit=
